WEBVTT

00:08.556 --> 00:11.357
♪ As the sun goes down ♪

00:11.359 --> 00:13.926
♪ And the shadows grow long ♪

00:13.928 --> 00:17.129
♪ Trying to find a gal
I can call my own ♪

00:17.131 --> 00:21.901
♪ Gettin' back on the road,
not a moment too soon... ♪

00:21.903 --> 00:24.637
Aunt Marta's gonna be
at the house 7:00 sharp,

00:24.639 --> 00:25.838
so you best be ready.

00:25.840 --> 00:27.340
You can't be late for school

00:27.342 --> 00:29.608
and she can't be late for work.

00:29.610 --> 00:31.277
No, you cannot walk home
with that boy.

00:31.279 --> 00:32.912
We've had this conversation.

00:32.914 --> 00:35.014
He's bad news.

00:36.451 --> 00:37.917
No.

00:37.919 --> 00:41.487
I have enough things
in my life to worry about

00:41.489 --> 00:44.557
without having to worry about...

00:48.031 --> 00:51.031
<b><font color=#00FF00>♪ NCIS:New Orleans 3x15 ♪</font></b>
<font color=#00FFFF>End of the Line</font>
Original Air Date on February 21, 2017

00:51.132 --> 00:53.599
♪ Boom, boom, boom, boom ♪

00:53.601 --> 00:56.302
♪ Bang, bang, bang, bang ♪

00:56.304 --> 00:58.804
♪ Boom, boom, boom, boom ♪

00:58.806 --> 01:01.040
♪ How, how, how, how ♪

01:01.042 --> 01:02.272
♪ Hey, hey ♪

01:02.281 --> 01:07.781
== sync, corrected by <font color=#00FF00>elderman</font> ==
<font color=#00FFFF>@elder_man</font>

01:07.782 --> 01:09.915
♪ You gotta come on. ♪

01:11.119 --> 01:13.285
<i>Okay, easy now.</i>

01:14.689 --> 01:16.188
Anytime you, uh,
you want to take a break,

01:16.190 --> 01:18.224
CJ, you know, just...
just let me know, okay?

01:18.226 --> 01:20.092
No, I'm good.
You okay?

01:20.094 --> 01:21.994
Yeah, I'm an NCIS agent now.
This is, you know...

01:21.996 --> 01:23.229
this is a piece of cake.

01:23.231 --> 01:24.764
Let's set it down.

01:24.766 --> 01:26.265
Yeah, that's a great idea.

01:27.335 --> 01:28.901
Just out of curiosity...
Huh?

01:28.903 --> 01:30.264
how'd you make it
through basic training again?

01:30.265 --> 01:30.829
That's...

01:30.853 --> 01:32.853
Got through from
studying and effort,

01:32.974 --> 01:34.874
both of which you could
use a little more of.

01:34.876 --> 01:36.575
I'm just trying to help, Mom.

01:36.577 --> 01:39.612
Only 'cause you want
Danny's room now that he's gone.

01:39.614 --> 01:42.014
Back to studying,
Math test tomorrow.

01:42.016 --> 01:43.349
Go.

01:43.351 --> 01:46.185
See you, newbie.

01:46.187 --> 01:48.254
I can't believe how fast
he's growing up, you know?

01:48.256 --> 01:51.590
I can't believe how fast
all my boys are growing up.

01:51.592 --> 01:55.494
Danny joining the Navy,
you at NCIS...

01:55.496 --> 01:57.830
Oh, thanks, Doc, you know
I feel the same about you.

01:57.832 --> 01:59.365
You're like the mother
that I never had.

01:59.367 --> 02:00.666
You have a mother, Sebastian.

02:00.668 --> 02:01.934
I've met her.

02:01.936 --> 02:03.903
Exactly.

02:03.905 --> 02:05.871
So, what, this gonna be
the Wade cave now?

02:05.873 --> 02:07.873
Hmm? 60-inch plasma maybe?

02:07.875 --> 02:09.208
Poker table,
a couple lava lamps?

02:09.210 --> 02:11.243
I was thinking art studio,
actually.

02:11.245 --> 02:14.346
I used to paint all the time
before I got married.

02:14.348 --> 02:15.781
Wait, wait, hold on.

02:15.783 --> 02:17.183
I never knew
you were married.

02:17.185 --> 02:20.920
Yes, I was.
A long time ago, different life.

02:20.922 --> 02:23.789
Have a look for yourself.

02:25.927 --> 02:27.526
Is this him?

02:27.528 --> 02:28.594
Reginald.

02:28.596 --> 02:30.096
Easy on the eye, isn't he?

02:30.098 --> 02:31.831
Yeah, look how beautiful
you were.

02:33.201 --> 02:35.568
That's... um, not that
you're not beautiful now.

02:35.570 --> 02:37.937
Obviously, you're... you're
very beautiful, it's just...

02:37.939 --> 02:38.904
you know, when you...

02:38.906 --> 02:40.840
It's all right, Sebastian.

02:40.842 --> 02:44.510
Reginald was a good man
when we first met.

02:44.512 --> 02:46.779
We had some good years
together...

02:46.781 --> 02:48.180
until we didn't.

02:50.151 --> 02:51.550
What happened?

02:51.552 --> 02:53.819
Let's just say he changed...

02:53.821 --> 02:56.122
not for the better.

03:00.728 --> 03:02.128
Duty calls.

03:02.130 --> 03:03.762
Looks like I've got a body.

03:03.764 --> 03:05.831
Yeah, NCIS.
It's probably the same body.

03:05.833 --> 03:07.199
You want to share a ride?

03:07.201 --> 03:09.969
Only if you don't ask
any more questions.

03:15.443 --> 03:17.810
These guys'll
take care of you.

03:17.812 --> 03:20.513
You'll be all right.

03:20.515 --> 03:21.814
She the first on scene?

03:21.816 --> 03:24.617
Streetcar driver, just
showing up for work.

03:24.619 --> 03:25.885
Not the best way
to start a day.

03:25.887 --> 03:27.286
About as grisly as it gets.

03:27.288 --> 03:28.354
Any witnesses?

03:28.356 --> 03:29.989
Not according to NOPD,

03:29.991 --> 03:31.924
but hopefully we got something
from these security cameras.

03:31.926 --> 03:32.958
Well, I doubt it.

03:32.960 --> 03:34.026
Killer placed the body

03:34.028 --> 03:36.328
directly behind
these streetcars,

03:36.330 --> 03:37.696
blocking all the cameras.

03:37.698 --> 03:39.265
I doubt the killer was
trying to avoid cameras.

03:39.267 --> 03:41.433
It's too specific
of a location.

03:41.435 --> 03:44.503
Profiler in me seems
to think that whoever it was

03:44.505 --> 03:45.538
was trying
to make a statement.

03:47.975 --> 03:50.509
Take it you don't want to ask
her out again, am I right?

03:50.511 --> 03:52.711
Blind date, high risk.

03:52.713 --> 03:54.747
I told you,
they're not worth dinner.

03:54.749 --> 03:56.815
Just drinks, and you definitely
don't give your number

03:56.817 --> 03:58.484
until you're sure
you like her.

03:58.486 --> 04:00.152
Is that you profiling,
Gregorio?

04:00.154 --> 04:01.620
That's me dating, amateur.

04:01.622 --> 04:03.689
Mm, I've dated plenty.
I'm not an amateur.

04:03.691 --> 04:04.890
Maybe a couple of hookups,

04:04.892 --> 04:06.325
but not potential
relationships.

04:06.327 --> 04:07.893
It's a whole different deal,

04:07.895 --> 04:10.796
and this whole airbrushed-photo
thing on dating apps...

04:10.798 --> 04:13.699
I mean, the only way to trigger
the yay or nay hormones

04:13.701 --> 04:16.168
is to have good,
old-fashioned eye contact.

04:16.170 --> 04:18.971
I never knew you
as a romantic, Gregorio.

04:18.973 --> 04:21.373
Profiling's not just
for finding criminals.

04:21.375 --> 04:23.342
Comes in handy, trust me.

04:25.613 --> 04:28.847
All I know so far is the
victim's Chief Karen Decker,

04:28.849 --> 04:30.583
based out of Belle Chasse.

04:30.585 --> 04:32.117
Still waiting on Loretta,

04:32.119 --> 04:33.619
so we can't take
the body down yet.

04:33.621 --> 04:35.020
Not a lot of blood
on the ground,

04:35.022 --> 04:36.322
considering all the stab wounds,

04:36.324 --> 04:38.157
which means she was killed
somewhere else,

04:38.159 --> 04:39.391
and then moved here.

04:39.393 --> 04:40.593
The question is, why here?

04:40.595 --> 04:42.027
Big risk...

04:42.029 --> 04:44.330
taking the time and effort
to string her up,

04:44.332 --> 04:46.031
not to mention the mutilation.

04:46.033 --> 04:47.733
Talking ritualistic?

04:47.735 --> 04:51.070
Crucifix pose indicates
she was meant to be a sacrifice.

04:51.072 --> 04:53.739
Eyes dug out so she couldn't
see her killer's soul.

04:53.741 --> 04:55.374
Okay, so, we figure out

04:55.376 --> 04:56.976
what she was sacrificed for,

04:56.978 --> 04:59.678
we might be able to ID
the lunatic who did this to her.

04:59.680 --> 05:01.413
My God.

05:03.951 --> 05:05.150
Loretta.

05:10.258 --> 05:11.523
Loretta, you all right?

05:11.525 --> 05:14.059
Please, get her down.

05:15.162 --> 05:16.662
Let's go find a ladder.

05:20.134 --> 05:22.201
Look, Gregorio,

05:22.203 --> 05:24.703
I'll check with Decker's C.O.,
all right?

05:24.705 --> 05:26.639
You take Christopher
and get with Patton,

05:26.641 --> 05:29.742
find out as much about her
as you can as fast as you can.

05:29.744 --> 05:31.477
Copy that.

05:31.479 --> 05:33.145
Tough to look at,
isn't it?

05:33.147 --> 05:36.115
I saw something like this
once before.

05:38.085 --> 05:40.919
I'd hoped never to see it again.

05:45.426 --> 05:49.662
Man, hard to believe anybody
would want to do her harm,

05:49.664 --> 05:51.297
especially that kind of harm.

05:51.299 --> 05:53.465
20-year vet,
unblemished record,

05:53.467 --> 05:55.601
Navy counselor who
helps other sailors.

05:55.603 --> 05:57.269
Yeah, a couple of
months from retiring,

05:57.271 --> 05:58.470
according to her record.

05:58.472 --> 06:00.072
About to start a new life.

06:00.074 --> 06:03.042
Only to have it stolen away
by some monster. Why?

06:03.044 --> 06:07.179
C.O. says Chief Decker got an
urgent call yesterday at noon,

06:07.181 --> 06:09.281
rushed out, never came back.

06:09.283 --> 06:10.449
Check her phone log?

06:10.451 --> 06:13.352
Putting it up
on the screen.

06:13.354 --> 06:15.954
Looks like the only incoming
call she got yesterday.

06:15.956 --> 06:18.924
But from the same caller
who called several days before.

06:18.926 --> 06:20.292
Can you trace that joker?

06:20.294 --> 06:21.760
Can't, burner cell.

06:21.762 --> 06:24.263
Powered down, too.
Or, more likely, destroyed.

06:24.265 --> 06:26.765
Well, any chance you can find
out where the call originated?

06:26.767 --> 06:28.767
Read my mind, bossman.

06:28.769 --> 06:31.370
There, pinged
from a cell tower

06:31.372 --> 06:33.605
across from the old
Peters Junior High School.

06:33.607 --> 06:35.140
Now, Peters has been
abandoned since Katrina,

06:35.142 --> 06:36.642
and who would want
to be hanging there?

06:36.644 --> 06:37.710
Obviously,
somebody who doesn't

06:37.712 --> 06:39.411
want to be found. Shall we?

06:39.413 --> 06:43.315
Keep me posted.
I'm gonna go to the morgue.

06:43.317 --> 06:45.851
See what Loretta knows.

06:47.000 --> 06:53.074
